{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: the failure is at a module handoff boundary (three collectors -> aggregation payload -> summary step), not a single pure function. REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: this can be caught with in-process fakes for the three source clients and a spy/stub summary adapter; real network/OS is not required for this specific behavior. LLM-DEP: disqualified by behavior text ('content passed to the summary-generation step') because it checks input assembly, not model judgment. MULTI-STEP: no chained agentic decisions.","test_description":"Wire real aggregation/orchestration modules with test doubles for metrics API, issue tracker API, and deployment log adapters; execute one report build; assert the exact payload sent to summary-generation contains all three source sections and expected key fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is cross-module error propagation (source adapter failure -> report assembler fallback note). Unit is too low because the bug appears in handoff/handling between modules. REAL-INFRA: unavailability can be simulated by adapter error/timeout exceptions in-process; no real OS/network needed to validate fallback logic. LLM-DEP: behavior checks fallback control path and section note presence, not summary quality. REJECTION-GATE for System: behavior text does not require validating real transport semantics, only correct fallback outcome.","test_description":"Run the report pipeline in-process with two source adapters returning normal data and one adapter failing deterministically; assert execution does not abort, output report includes a `data unavailable` marker in the failed source section, and other sections remain populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness depends on what the real summary model writes (factual inclusion/accuracy of key values). A deterministic stub would always pass and hide misrepresentation errors (deterministic-assertion trap). MULTI-STEP: this behavior is about one model-output quality check, not a multi-agent chain. REJECTION-GATE for Integration: behavior text requires 'accurately represents' narrative content, which cannot be validated with fixed mock outputs.","test_description":"Use real summary-generation model calls on a curated set of weekly inputs with known key values; score outputs against factual checks (required values present, no value inversion, no omitted critical metric beyond threshold); fail on factual mismatch rate above acceptance threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: this behavior explicitly requires end-to-end delivery to an inbox, which depends on real email transport/inbox behavior; mocks can hide SMTP/API auth, MIME formatting, and delivery path issues. LLM-DEP: not required by this behavior text; it asserts transport success to recipient inbox, not model output quality. MULTI-STEP agentic sequencing is not the